# Service Account Name Helper

The `mimir.serviceAccountName` helper produces:

```
mimir
```

When the release name is "mimir", the template follows this logic:

1. If `serviceAccount.create` is true, it uses either the custom name from `serviceAccount.name` or defaults to `mimir.fullname` (which evaluates to "mimir")
2. If `serviceAccount.create` is false, it uses the custom name or defaults to "default"

Since the default behavior creates the service account and uses the full name, the output is **"mimir"**.

Here's the relevant template section:

```mustache
{{- define "mimir.serviceAccountName" -}}
{{- if .Values.serviceAccount.create -}}
    {{ default (include "mimir.fullname" .) .Values.serviceAccount.name }}
{{- else -}}
    {{ default "default" .Values.serviceAccount.name }}
{{- end -}}
{{- end -}}
```
